[3]
Date: Wed, 26 Oct 2005 17:46:18 GMT-3
From: Luz Alba Fornells <luzalba@bioqmed.ufrj.br>
Source: Folha online, Brazil 26 Oct 2005 [in Portuguese, trans. by JW, edited]
<http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/folha/dinheiro/ult91u101734.shtml>

There are now 11 confirmed foci of FMD in Mato Grosso do Sul state (MS).
According to the Director of the department of animal health, the
government is still awaiting the result of lab tests from 2 more suspected
foci in MS and 4 in Parana state (PR), which will be available on Friday
[28 Oct 2005].
The 11th focus was found on a small property in Eldorado township near the
Vezozzo ranch, where the 1st focus was found this month, close to the
borders of Paraguay, and of Sao Paulo & Parana states, Brazil. See map at:
<http://www.oie.int/cartes/BRA051021.gif>.
3 out of 24 cattle were sick; all have been slaughtered.
--
Luz Alba Fornells, PhD
Nucleus for Investigating Emerging Infectious Diseases
Institute of Medical Biochemistry
Center for Health Sciences
Federal University of Rio de Janeiro
Brazil
<luzalba@bioqmed.ufrj.br>
[This disease is very easily spread, and the movement of animals will move
the disease. The disease can spread by the wind carrying viral particles to
a new location. Biosecurity should be strictly maintained, and every
vehicle, person, or anything else moving onto or off of these problems
should be thoroughly disinfected. - Mod.TG]
